    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="227"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1959: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-09T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 9, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6232. Tehran reports political situation has grown worse largely due to
                    obstruction by Majlis. Worsening food shortage has brought on new crisis which
                    threatens to cause fall of Qavam cabinet or dissolution of Majlis. Widespread
                    rioting occurred in Tehran December 8.</p>
                <p>As we have repeatedly stated, Department strongly favors continuance in power of
                    present cabinet, even though it may be unsatisfactory in some respects, rather
                    than a change to another group which might prove even more unsatisfactory and
                    which would command even less popular support.</p>
                <p>Please communicate substance of above to Foreign Office and let us have any
                    comments British Government may care to offer in this regard.</p>
                <p>Please also advise Foreign Office our reports indicate food situation in Iran
                    still deteriorating and we hope British authorities will press their efforts not
                    only with respect to shipment of wheat from North American ports but also in
                    connection with possible advances of grain from near-by territories in Middle
                    East.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
